postcontent:
I have for sale, two solvent trap adapters for use with an AR-15 standard 1/2x28 threads. These parts are 100% legal to own and sell as they are to be used as a solvent trap adapter. If you thread an oil filter onto your rifle and fire a round through it, the filter and adapter become a suppressor and therefore are no longer ATF compliant. DO NOT DO THIS, IT IS ILLEGAL. However, as a solvent trap adapter, you can use an oil filter to catch all of your used patches and stop your brushes from spraying solvent all over the place when they exit the barrel. title: For Trade:  Sigarms (Sig Sauer) sp 2340
postcontent:
For Trade Only.  I have a Sig 2340 in 40 cal.  This firearm is the predecessor of the 2022 and most of the parts are interchangeable (not the barrel incidentally) and it takes the same magazines.  It is DA/SA with a decocker and external hammer, extra backstrap, 2 magazines, and a hard case.  It is in excellent shape and has no wear on the finish at all with the exception of standard operational wear on the barrel's finish (shown in photo).  The only issue is that the gun carry case is missing a latch and it does not have the manual.  It is a very accurate gun my only issue with it is that I am a smaller framed man and the ergonomics for me and my smaller hands can be a bit tricky.  I am looking for even trades of similar quality and value; I cannot add money on top (limited finances).  I am interested in semi autos primarily though I do have a soft spot for SP 101's.  Send me an e-mail of what you have to trade and, if I am interested, we'll get in touch.

     I have been asked what the difference is between the 2340 and the 2022 so, here goes.  You could consider the weapons to be generations 1 and 2 respectively of the Sig Pro line.  The line was originally designed as a less expensive option for law enforcement and civilian shooters as many could not afford the 8-900 dollar price tag of the Sig classic line.  At the time of the first design, rails tended to be proprietary as there was not yet an industry standard.  Thus, the 2340 wears a proprietary rail unique to Sig (incidentally, there are adapters to convert this rail to standard specs as Sig didn't update their design till 2004-2005).  In 2005 (I believe this was the date, I don't have my resources in from of me) the french government put in an order for the Sig pro line to arm both military and police contingent on some updates.  Incidentally, it was also during this time that sig did some shuffling around with ownership and branding and the US subsidiary went from the brand Sigarms back to Sig Sauer (though you still see literature and other things still bearing the name Sigarms).  The updates given to the Sig pro line were both to satisfy the french contract and to bring the polymer line up to speed with the tastes of the market.  So the Sig 2022 has the following updates:  A slightly different barrel link design, an external extractor( the 2340 has an internal extractor), a standard accessory rail, and a squared trigger guard (the 2340 has a “classic” sig profiled guard).  Both weapons are made with a polymer frame, stainless steel for the major components which is then coated in a black matte finish, they both have the standard decocker and hammer, and they have interchangeable back straps (these,as far as I am aware, are interchangeable between generations).

title: For Sale:  Scam warning
postcontent:
Beware of scams. I have had three in the last month. Not sure, but probably originating in Nigeria. Had a response supposedly from a Debbie Scott, to a rifle I have listed. Song and dance, son was hurt in military, likes the rifle, will send cashiers check with more than enough to cover shipping, blah, blah, blah. Even after responding to her email, advising her that I would only ship to her FFL dealer after confirmation of FFL license, I received a check from the Bevard County Tax Collector in Titusville, Fl.  I called the tax collector in Florida, to confirm my suspicions, and sure enough, it is counterfeit.
No return address on envelope but does show a business address in Tucson Az.
